===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|Scandinavia|Scandināvia|lang=la}}, from {{proto|Germanic|Skaþinawjō|Scadia island|lang=en}} (compare {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|Scedenig|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|Skaney|lang=non}} 'southern tip of Sweden'), from *-''aujo'' 'island' (compare {{etyl|ang|-}} ''ī(e)g'' 'island', {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|ey}} 'island').

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|eɪviə}}

